  "prompt": "What are the legal precedents related to money laundering cases?",
  "response": "There are various legal precedents related to money laundering cases. Some key cases include:\n\n1. United States v. Munsingwear (Supreme Court)\n- Established procedural guidelines for money laundering prosecutions\n\n2. Bank of Credit and Commerce International (BCCI) case\n- Major international money laundering investigation\n- Led to significant reforms in banking regulations\n\n3. United States v. Santos (Supreme Court)\n- Clarified definition of \"proceeds\" in money laundering statutes\n\n4. Black Money Case (India)\n- Landmark case addressing offshore financial transactions\n\n5. R v. Anwoir (UK)\n- Established threshold for proving money laundering intent\n\n6. Basel Committee Guidelines\n- International standards for anti-money laundering practices\n\nThese cases have shaped legal interpretations and enforcement strategies. However, specific details can vary by jurisdiction and context.\n\nWould you be interested in discussing a particular aspect of money laundering legal precedents?",
